@startuml
title Viaverse Notification / Inbox / Channel Delivery — Component Diagram

component "KMP / Next.js Client\nInbox\nBadge count\nNotification settings" as Client
component "API Gateway / App BFF\nInbox API\nPreferences API" as BFF
component "Notification Event Consumer" as Consumer
component "NotificationController\nPreferenceController" as Controller
component "Notification Use Cases\nCreateNotification\nDispatchNotification\nMarkRead\nSendBroadcast" as UseCases
component "Notification Policies\npreference\nquiet hours\nrate limits\npriority/digest" as Policies
component "Ports\nInboxRepo\nDeviceRepo\nTemplatePort\nPushPort\nEmailSmsPort\nOutboxPort" as Ports
component "identity-service\npreferences\nlocale\ndevice tokens" as Identity
component "Provider Adapters\nFCM\nAPNs\nNetgsm\nSMTP" as Providers
database "PostgreSQL\nnotification\nnotification_attempt\ndevice_token\npreference" as DB
queue "Kafka / Outbox\nDomain events\nNotificationSent\nNotificationFailed" as Kafka
component "Scheduler / Retry Worker\nbackoff\ndigest\nquiet-hour release" as Scheduler

Client --> BFF : HTTPS
BFF --> Controller : REST
Kafka ..> Consumer : consume
Consumer --> UseCases : event command
Controller --> UseCases : command/query
UseCases --> Policies : validate
Policies --> Ports : ports
Policies --> Identity : prefs/locale/devices
Ports --> Providers : send
Ports --> DB : persist
UseCases --> Kafka : delivery events
Scheduler ..> UseCases : retry/digest command

note bottom
Domain services publish business events only.
Notification service decides who receives what,
through which channel, and when.
end note
@enduml
